{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 2280428, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Reignac", "body": "Meryl is awesome and it's awesome that we're finally seeing him in-game.\r\n\r\nHe's undead, but he's not a Forsaken. Meryl died in the Troll Wars 2,800 years ago and raised himself from the dead with his own magic. He was a founding member of the Council of Tirisfal, and so has worked alongside every single Guardian of Tirisfal starting from the very first one, [url=http://legion.wowhead.com/npc=102846/alodi]Alodi[/url].\r\n\r\nIn the comic, Meryl was entrusted by [url=http://legion.wowhead.com/npc=46323/garona-halforcen]Garona[/url] to watch over her son, Med'an. In Legion we also learn that Garona gave him her daggers to hide away back then too, which are the Assassination Rogue Artifacts. Meryl freed [url=http://legion.wowhead.com/npc=98102/valeera-sanguinar]Valeera Sanguinar[/url] from the dreadlord [url=http://legion.wowhead.com/npc=102785/kathranatir]Kathra'Natir[/url], who was possessing her, by taking the demon inside his own body instead. But he's such a badass he didn't get possessed, and was able to hold back Kathra'Natir's will. Ever since then he's been traveling the world to find a way to get rid of Kathra'Natir for good.", "date": "2015-11-25T18:21:08-06:00", "rating": 50, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
